Can you remove this one now that we have the iff?
Similarly here

```suggestion
theorem Commute.of_orderOf_dvd_two [IsCancelMul G] (h : âˆ€ g : G, orderOf g âˆ£ 2) :
    âˆ€ a b : G, Commute a b := by
```

I feel like you should not have this definition at all since it's just a call to a constructor with only one use of each argument

EDIT: I see this was moved. Can you put a `TODO: Delete` then?
That's just the rewriting lemma for `Commute`, right?
No, you also need to unfold `SemiconjBy`
You can use a `Commute a b` inside of a `rw`, but you can't easily `rw` in a `Commute a b` without first unfolding `Commute` *and* `SemiConjBy`
`G` should be implicit in `exponent_dvd` since it's an iff

This first condition is redundant
```suggestion
theorem exists_orderOf_eq_exponent (hG : ExponentExists G) :
```
Only if you assume cancellativity, as far as I can tell. If not, please prove :)

This is true in *any* monoid, almost by definition. I would put these right before `Monoid.exponent_ne_zero`.
```lean
@[to_additive]
theorem ExponentExists.isOfFinOrder (h : ExponentExists G) (g : G) : IsOfFinOrder g :=
  isOfFinOrder_iff_pow_eq_one.mpr <| by peel 2 h; exact this g

@[to_additive]
theorem ExponentExists.orderOf_pos (h : ExponentExists G) (g : G) : 0 < orderOf g :=
  h.isOfFinOrder g |>.orderOf_pos
```
you can use the latter to golf this proof too:
```lean
theorem exponent_eq_zero_of_order_zero {g : G} (hg : orderOf g = 0) : exponent G = 0 :=
  exponent_eq_zero_iff.mpr fun h â†¦ h.orderOf_pos g |>.ne' hg
```

I think it would be nice to keep this around without the deprecation
```suggestion
@[to_additive]
theorem exponent_dvd_of_forall_pow_eq_one (n : â„•) (hG : âˆ€ g : G, g ^ n = 1) :
    exponent G âˆ£ n :=
```
Can we make it an alias then?
This lemma got merged in-between: [commute_iff_eq](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Commute/Defs.html#commute_iff_eq)

```suggestion
  ExponentExists.of_finite.isTorsion
```
Why not use dot notation all the way?
`_root_.ExponentExists.isTorsion` doesn't work in dot notation because it's about `Monoid.ExponentExists`. (I don't want to deal with that in this PR.)
Oh yeah that's why

I'm willing to bet this is more useful in practice:
```suggestion
theorem ExponentExists.isOfFinOrder (h : ExponentExists G) {g : G} : IsOfFinOrder g :=
```
Can you make that an `alias` of `exponent_dvd_iff_forall_pow_eq_one` (and make `G` implicit in `exponent_dvd_iff_forall_pow_eq_one`)?
`exponent_dvd_of_forall_pow_eq_one` is no longer deprecated, so I guess I'll revert changes like this
